sys_ui_annotation.text: The Supplier and Financial details below are required by the Reserve Bank for the Compendium and must be accurate entered into the BS11 Sharepoint within 15 days of the contract being entered into

Enter the values for the functions/services on this Form (not the whole relationship for the supplier). SoW should be individually assessed, unless similar services. If more than one SOW, please split values based on SOW (attach analysis if necessary)

Your answers in this section should concentrate on 'inherent risk' at this stage ie. it should consider what the impact of the event or incident would be, before you take any steps to mitigate or manage it. So, before any service or disaster recovery or business continuity plans you or the supplier have in place are activated. For each of the Outcomes below, state the impact on Kiwibank's business operations and/or its customers in the event the supplier is unable to deliver the required service/system, either temporarily or permanently?

This section should show your evidence and assessment of it. 'Refer to attached' is NOT an acceptable response. If you require further guidance please discuss with your Op Risk and Compliance team and refer to the BCP Guidance on the Compliance with Outsourcing Requirements (BS11) OurSpace page.

This section should show your evidence and assessment of it. 'Refer to attached' is NOT an acceptable response. If you require further guidance, if you have an IT person dealing with the supplier for this service, refer to IT. If the service is part of a service categorised as Platinum or Gold, you should liaise with the IT BCP/DR specialist. Otherwise consult your Operational Risk and Compliance team. Refer to the BCP/DR Guidance on the Compliance with Outsourcing Requirements (BS11) OurSpace page.

Considering the BCP and DR sections above, answer the following. If it is not feasible for the BCP/DR to be in place and tested before the contract is signed, satisfactory BCP/DR evidence may be put in place after signing but before the service is implemented. You will need to monitor accordingly.
The Reserve Bank requires specific clauses to be included, and for additional steps if these are amended, or if the contract is based overseas
Please provide applicable section reference in the MSA, SAA SDA or SoW
